FBIS4-5657 "dreas071_a_94015" FBIS-EAS-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Bank Extends $200 Million Loan to Mexico Bank Extends $200 Million Loan to Mexico OW1204141194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1343 GMT 12 Apr 94 OW1204141194 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, April 12 KYODO -- The Export-Import Bank of Japan said Tuesday [12 April] it has signed a protocol for an untied direct loan of up to 200 million U.S. dollars to Nacional Financiera S.N.C. (Nafin) of Mexico. The funds will be used for financing such projects as installing emissions control facilities to reduce air pollution in the Mexico City area, the Japanese bank said. The funds are being extended in line with Japan's "Funds for Development" initiative program launched last June, the bank said.
